	   <tr><td colspan=2>Good info.<br><br>I have further modified my assist hotkey.  I actually assist the secondary tank of our group.  The reason is that for some reason, assisting the main tank/puller has sent my pet after a different mob than the tank actually is focused upon.  I think it's a timing issue.  However, the secondary tank, being a human player, targets the correct mob (usually at least) almost every time since he/she is assisting the primary tank.<br><br>Further, if the group's cleric gets aggroed, I tell my pet to back off whoever it was fighting and send them after the mob.  If enchanters are in the group, they usually mez the mob.  However, if you don't have an enchanter and the cleric is getting pummeled, this tactic helps a lot.  This is also one of those time you may purposely burn hard to pull the aggro off the cleric.<br><br>Nazmag Manamatrix<br>32nd Season on Povar<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
